Storyline: 
The 3-D action-thriller Sanctum, from executive producer James Cameron, follows a
team of underwater cave divers on a treacherous expedition to the largest, most
beautiful and least accessible cave system on Earth. When a tropical storm forces
them deep into the caverns, they must fight raging water, deadly terrain and
creeping panic as they search for an unknown escape route to the sea. Master diver
Frank McGuire (Richard Roxburgh) has explored the South Pacific's Esa-ala Caves
for months. But when his exit is cut off in a flash flood, Frank's team--including
17-year-old son Josh (Rhys Wakefield) and financier Carl Hurley
(Ioan Gruffudd)--are forced to radically alter plans. With dwindling supplies, the
crew must navigate an underwater labyrinth to make it out. Soon, they are
confronted with the unavoidable question: Can they survive, or will they
be trapped forever?
